<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 2:30PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Anson
and Stanly Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 229 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Midland, or 9 miles southeast of Downtown Concord, moving east at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Ansonville, Plyler, Fairview In Union County, Locust,
Norwood, Badin, Oakboro, Stanfield and Morrow Mountain State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
